-- STOCKS NEWS US-Wall St cuts losses as Apple lead Nasdaq higher
-- 
-- Mon May 05, 2014 10:47AM EDT
-- None



May 5 (Reuters) - Wall Street is trimming its earlier losses with Apple shares leading the tech-heavy Nasdaq index higher.

Apple Inc <AAPL.O> shares are up 0.7 percent at $597, nearing the $600 mark that the stock hasn't hit since late 2012. The stock could face more volatility as major global hedge funds are set to meet at 19th Annual Ira Sohn Investment Conference later in the day. Apple has traditionally been a darling among top U.S. hedge funds in recent years. Index snapshot at 10:39:27: * S&P 500 <.SPX> is falling 2.32 points, 0.12 percent. * Nasdaq Comp <.IXIC> is down 0.788 points, 0.02 percent. * Dow industrials <.DJI> are down 39.7 points, 0.24 percent. * Russell 2000 <.TOY> is falling 3.92 points, 0.35 percent. * S&P MidCap <.IDX> is down 0.99 points, 0.07 percent. * S&P SmallCap <.SPCY> is off 2.48 points, 0.38 percent.  From earlier in the day: 10:09 - Put contracts are flying in the options market in the early going Monday as stocks open the week broadly lower.  The weekly contracts on the SPDR S&P 500 ETF Trust <SPY.P> that expire coming Friday are among the most active, with 4,000 put contracts opening on the $174.50 strike across multiple exchanges for 2 cents per contract, according to options analytics firm Trade Alert. Currently, the SPDR S&P 500 ETF is down 0.5 percent at $187.20. On the Powershares QQQ Trust Series 1 <QQQ.P>, more than 2,000 put contracts are traded on the May $86 strike that expire on Friday, for 44 cents apiece. The ETF is down 0.2 percent at $87.30. Index snapshot at 10:05 a.m.: * S&P 500 <.SPX> down 0.4 percent * Dow industrials <.DJI> down 0.57 percent * Nasdaq composite <.IXIC> down .4 percent  From earlier in the day: 09:40 - Bank stocks are leading Wall Street lower in early morning session on Monday. Late Friday, JPMorgan <JPM.N> said the investment bank expects second-quarter revenue from bond and equity trading to decline in the second quarter by about 20 percent from a year earlier.  JPMorgan is off 2.6 percent at $54.15, Bank of America <BAC.N> is down 1.2 percent at $15.05 and Goldman Sachs <GS.N> is off 2.3 percent at $155.50. Index snapshot at 9:35: * S&P 500 <.SPX> is falling 14.25 points, 0.76 percent. * Nasdaq Comp <.IXIC> is down 36.733 points, 0.89 percent. * Dow industrials <.DJI> are down 124.3 points, 0.75 percent. * Russell 2000 <.TOY> is falling 13.22 points, 1.17 percent. * S&P MidCap <.IDX> is down 13.76 points, 1.01 percent. * S&P SmallCap <.SPCY> is off 6.69 points, 1.02 percent.From earlier in the day:  09:18 - With the market near record levels, investors bracing for a technical selloff in equities are snapping up volatility products to hedge against a decline. In early morning trading on Monday, Credit Suisse AG - VelocityShares Daily 2x VIX Short Term ETNs <TVIX.O> are among the most actively traded securities, up 2.2 percent with more than 200,000 contracts changing hands. TVIX has lost nearly 20 percent of its value so far this year and over 90 percent in the last few years as the bull market roared. Industry data released on Friday showed equity fund managers trimmed their long positions while speculators trimmed their net shorts in S&P 500 futures contracts in the week ended April 29, according to the Commodity Futures Trading Commision. [ID:nEMS0D46GO]   Long  Short Net   -------------------------------------------  Fund Managers 296,38195,608   200,773 Speculators   106,527   168,982   -62,455 From earlier in the day: 08:32 - Target Corp <TGT.N> shares are climbing the most active list before the bell and are off 1.5 percent on news the retailer's Chief Executive and Chairman Gregg Steinhafel is leaving in the wake of the last year's devastating data breach. [ID:nL2N0NR0B5] Pfizer Inc <PFE.N> shares are also down in premarket action, off 0.8 percent after first-quarter results that were well below Wall Street expectations on falling sales of generic medicines. The company also said it may sweeten its offer for rival AstraZeneca. [ID:nL2N0NR094] For more on the day's premarket action click [XHR/US].  From earlier in the day: 08:02 - U.S. index futures are all lower Monday morning with the focus largely on overseas factors - more evidence of slowing momentum in the Chinese economy and escalating tension in Ukraine. * S&P 500 e-minis <ESc1> are down 7.25 points, about 0.39 percent, with about 120,000 contracts traded. * Nasdaq 100 e-minis <NQ1> are down 0.43 percent, or 15.25 points, on volume of nearly 23,000 contracts.